# Musk Muscles His Rivals Out In Space Race

Concerns Rise as U.S. Relies on SpaceX

## By ERIC LIPFON

WASHINGTON — Elon Musk, the aerospace firm’s owner, is on top of the space launch business over the past two decades, continuing engineering genius and an entrepreneurial drive with a demand that the U.S. government is playing a leading role, this down-sizing contract that had long dominated the American space race.

Today, it is Mr. Musk who is descending. In his company, SpaceX, is the primary provider of launch services to NASA and to the Pentagon. His rockets carry far more mass than satellites into orbit than any aerospace craft, including the two to low Earth orbit satellites that the U.S. government is operating from within its own space domain.

But one striking way, the former outside has come to interest the aerospace contractor because it once fought to topple it.
